metadata.name: Morathi
metadata.description:
A portrait of Paniya tribes ,they are commonly called as Morathi and they live in Wayanad ,Kerala ,India. Those ear rings are a special jewellery made by these tribals by using Rosary pea ,the outer covering is made by folding palm leaves. The outermost is the skin which got enlarged by the action of those leaves. Wayanad is a place where there is a wide range of tribals. This was shot from a tribal festival called Valliyoorkkavu temple festival in 2018.
